52.7	Howl's_Moving_Castle_(film)	Howl's Moving Castle (film)	Howl's Moving Castle Hauru no Ugoku Shiro) is a 2004 Japanese animated (anime) action drama film written and directed by Hayao Miyazaki of Studio Ghibli and based on the novel of the same name by Diana Wynne Jones. Mamoru Hosoda, director of one episode and two movies from the Digimon series, was originally selected to direct but abruptly left the project, leaving the then-retired Miyazaki to take up the director's role.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a0/Howls-moving-castleposter.jpg/215px-Howls-moving-castleposter.jpg
